story.storyDescription: Luke: Don’t go to school tomorrow.
story.title: Don't Go to School

messages.text: If I don’t go, I don’t play.
Sorry man...can’t give up that spot.
Trust me. Don’t go to school tomorrow.
Why you pushing for me to skip school?
I don’t want to say. Just don’t go.
Shit...is there a test in Physics?
DO. NOT. GO. TO. SCHOOL. TOMORROW.
I need a good reason not to score the winning point tomorrow. :p
You’re acting real serious about this.
You can’t go to school tomorrow because...
IF THEY DON’T SHOOT YOU FIRST
AND THEN YOU GO TO JAIL
Luke look.  I can’t let you do this.
I’ve had this planned since October.
Luke what’s going on?  why would you do this?
People with hearts and fingers and lives and goals.
These people could ruin my life
Everyone I know thinks you’re mad cool
Pat, Jared, Scott, they look up to you
I’ve heard teachers say how you “shine” in class
I don’t know what you’re talking about
What??  When do you ever interact with them?
A party a few days ago.
Oh the one I couldn’t make?
Because I thought Joel was over by my drink, but I didn’t think anything of it.
And then I felt weird and woozy.
And then Abby was trying to make out with me.
But I could barely stand up and I felt like a moron.
I could barely stand and I was supposed to kiss her?
And then Monica dropped my pants.
And Sam and Mark took pix.
I don’t know what they did with them.
But if that goes on the Internet...
So tell someone what they did.
I don’t think you understand the seriousness of what you’re doing.
You plan to KILL THESE PEOPLE
They’ll never walk the halls again
Never say hi to their parents
You can’t take this back man.
As your friend, I can’t let you do this.
Well they can’t have the opportunity to ruin my life
They haven’t. You don’t know where those pix are.
Or what they’re going to do with them.
Why would I talk to them?????
They shouldn’t have messed with me.
I can’t let you do this.
Dude, I have to call the cops.
But I can’t withhold information like this...
People’s lives are on the line
WHAT KIND OF FRIEND ARE YOU
IF YOU CALL THE COPS I GO TO JAIL
AND THOSE PICTURES CAN STILL CIRCULATE
I CAN’T WATCH THE NEWS AS COPS DRAG YOU OUT OF THE HIGH SCHOOL
I’D BE NO BETTER THAN YOU IF I SAT BACK AND WATCHED
Why don’t you man up, go to school, and protect them all?
If you want to be a hero, that’s the way to do it.
That’s so messed up! Do you know what you’re saying????
This isn’t about being a hero.
It’s about doing the right thing.
If you call the cops I’ll shoot myself.
Now we’re playing with ethical dilemmas.
Do I save the greatest number of people and call the cops?
Or do I stick by my best friend and let five innocent people die tomorrow?
I DON’T KNOW WHAT YOU WANT ME TO SAY
I GET IT AND WHAT THEY DID WAS WRONG
AND IT’S NOT FAIR BUT WHAT YOU’RE GOING TO DO DOESN’T EVEN THINGS OUT
I’m involved and I don’t want to be.
I’m not going to school tomorrow man.
You’re my friend, those people aren’t bad people, and I can’t watch any of this happen
